  "time_ut": 1657307847,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba9\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Review of List of Prohibited Companies",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "External Affairs Minister Professor G.L. said that the government is focusing on reviewing the list of organizations and individuals banned under United Nations regulations, the release of prisoners detained under the Anti-Terrorism Act, and the implementation of the proposed 21st Amendment to the Constitution. Peiris said.",
        "External Affairs Minister Professor G.L. Peiris had recently met with EU Ambassador in Colombo, Denis Saibi.",
        "During this discussion, developments related to the current economic situation, the 2012 United Nations Regulation No. Minister Peiris briefed the EU envoy on the review of the list of entities and individuals proscribed under Article 1, the release of prisoners detained under the Anti-Terrorism Act, progress made by independent institutions and the proposed 21st Amendment to the Constitution.",
        "The minister stressed that the government has made verifiable and measurable progress through established domestic mechanisms and is focused on delivering the necessary political reforms despite the current economic crisis.",
        "The minister further informed that the government intends to present a new budget soon which will include various welfare measures aimed at the weaker sections of the society.",
        "Next EU GSP for 2024 \u2013 2033 The regulation is currently being discussed in the EU Commission and the EU Parliament, the ambassador said.",
        "The recently concluded UN Minister Peiris stated that Sri Lanka will continue its constructive engagement with the members of the Human Rights Council, including the 50th session of the Human Rights Council."
      ],
